Cape Town -  The Western Cape Department of Transport and Public Works (DTPW) has now revealed said that the Franschhoek Pass is now reopened for traffic. After a rockfall on 22 June 2019, the DTPW closed the Franschhoek Pass for safety reasons. A car had ended up being crushed by rockfalls caused by torrential rain and  gale force winds. "The pass will officially be opened by the MEC of Transport and Public Works, Bonginkosi Madikizela on a date and time to be confirmed. Further details on this opening will be shared by the Ministry in due course." Cape Argus